        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-29T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-29T22:00:00-05:00" n="1116" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1116">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1121 McMillan, Archibald/8–3045:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-30T10:00:00+07:00">August 30, 1945—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 31—11:17 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1469. McMillan informed Embassy today that some time ago Supreme Court rules [<hi rend="italic">ruled</hi>] that previous decisions in his case were incorrect
                    and sent case back to Szechuan high court for retrial. Case was retried in high
                    court here August 22 and court’s decision was announced August 28, [it] reversed
                    previous decisions and rendered verdict of not guilty.</p>
                <p>New part of developments and copy of high court’s decision will be forwarded air
                        mail.<note n="9" xml:id="d1116fn9">Not found in Department files.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hurley</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
